01:35:26,434 --> 01:35:32,203
Excuse me father, but you look like
the lord of the Great House.

794
01:35:32,412 --> 01:35:37,720
Well! And that is not
as strange as you think!

795
01:35:37,924 --> 01:35:42,491
I just... tell your mother
I wish to see her.

796
01:35:42,700 --> 01:35:46,152
Yes father. Can you spare me a moment?

797
01:35:46,363 --> 01:35:48,686
I must know what seed
to prepare for the Summer planting.

798
01:35:48,890 --> 01:35:52,715
Why trouble me about it?
Prepare the seed my son gives you!

799
01:36:00,403 --> 01:36:02,573
These flowers are dead, Little One!

800
01:36:02,644 --> 01:36:05,776
Your sister knows only happiness.

801
01:36:05,986 --> 01:36:10,437
Mother!
Is it a letter from your brother?

802
01:36:10,880 --> 01:36:15,540
No mother! Father wishes to see you.

803
01:36:17,787 --> 01:36:20,252
Forgot how chilly it was!

804
01:36:22,563 --> 01:36:28,530
Are you well? Your pain, is it bad?

805
01:36:29,010 --> 01:36:32,966
No it's nothing!

806
01:36:46,056 --> 01:36:47,616
You sent for me?

807
01:36:48,194 --> 01:36:51,429
Well, there's a thing I've done,

808
01:36:51,634 --> 01:36:53,660
I bought the Great House!

809
01:36:53,871 --> 01:36:55,840
The house of Loo!

810
01:36:56,041 --> 01:36:58,522
Courts and land!

811
01:36:58,734 --> 01:37:02,689
I'm the new lord there.

812
01:37:03,670 --> 01:37:07,976
Well? Have you no thanks?

813
01:37:08,180 --> 01:37:10,978
I thought it would please you
to be mistress in that house,

814
01:37:10,986 --> 01:37:16,825
where you lived as a slave.

815
01:37:17,031 --> 01:37:19,466
Our sons were born here...

816
01:37:19,667 --> 01:37:21,289
They must have wives!

817
01:37:21,498 --> 01:37:23,517
We'll have grandchildren,

818
01:37:23,725 --> 01:37:25,886
there's room in that house to all!

819
01:37:26,094 --> 01:37:30,808
You'll have a high place
with money to spend for slaves.

820
01:37:31,018 --> 01:37:32,513
You must make yourself becoming to it!

821
01:37:32,717 --> 01:37:36,100
Look at your hair! Your clothes!

822
01:37:36,104 --> 01:37:37,633
You disgrace me!

823
01:37:37,641 --> 01:37:40,964
One would think you're still the
wife of a common labourer!

824
01:37:42,951 --> 01:37:46,035
Wear the pearl you have.

825
01:37:46,244 --> 01:37:51,200
The pearls? I have them!

826
01:37:51,345 --> 01:37:53,485
You would never wear them.

827
01:37:53,486 --> 01:37:55,386
Why...

828
01:37:55,820 --> 01:37:59,827
I look at them sometimes.

829
01:37:59,829 --> 01:38:05,797
I need them, give them to me.

830
01:38:29,770 --> 01:38:35,416
I know that I'm ugly,
and not to be loved.

831
01:38:40,535 --> 01:38:43,030
All that we have now came from you.

832
01:38:43,241 --> 01:38:46,942
That is the truth and I say it.

833
01:38:47,149 --> 01:38:49,120
But, but now...

834
01:38:49,321 --> 01:38:52,053
But now?

835
01:38:52,259 --> 01:38:57,783
There's a woman, not such a one as you;

836
01:38:57,992 --> 01:39:02,652
not as good as you,
it's like a sickness!

837
01:39:02,860 --> 01:39:07,301
When I'm with her, it's not enough!

838
01:39:07,502 --> 01:39:10,612
When I'm not with her, there's nothing!

839
01:39:10,826 --> 01:39:14,133
Even the land is nothing!

840
01:39:14,338 --> 01:39:19,801
Then it will be better
when she's in your house.

841
01:39:20,378 --> 01:39:22,237
You'll say that?

842
01:39:22,439 --> 01:39:26,396
Is it your wish?

843
01:39:26,942 --> 01:39:29,412
Yes.

844
01:39:29,613 --> 01:39:33,348
Let it be then!

845
01:39:33,555 --> 01:39:39,523
Ou lang, what is there more to say?

846
01:39:42,708 --> 01:39:45,668
Nothing.

847
01:40:26,186 --> 01:40:28,650
Who is it?

848
01:40:36,385 --> 01:40:40,448
Who is that man going out the gate?

849
01:40:40,461 --> 01:40:46,571
He look something like my son, Lung!

850
01:41:20,101 --> 01:41:21,564
Now then what?

851
01:41:21,565 --> 01:41:23,318
I'm Ching the farmer.

852
01:41:23,327 --> 01:41:25,324
Well, Ching the farmer what?

853
01:41:25,529 --> 01:41:27,864
I have business with Wong the farmer.

854
01:41:28,068 --> 01:41:29,628
Wong the farmer?

855
01:41:29,839 --> 01:41:31,535
This is the great house of Wong!

856
01:41:31,743 --> 01:41:35,706
He's the lord here!

857
01:42:07,855 --> 01:42:11,343
There's a bad woman in the house!

858
01:42:11,549 --> 01:42:14,383
There's a bad woman in the house!

859
01:42:14,621 --> 01:42:17,558
Bad woman!

860
01:42:17,759 --> 01:42:19,894
Father, hush!

861
01:42:19,898 --> 01:42:22,165
It's his second wife.

862
01:42:22,169 --> 01:42:24,602
I say it's a bad woman!

863
01:42:24,808 --> 01:42:29,010
I had but one woman...
and my father had but one woman,

864
01:42:29,066 --> 01:42:30,413
and we farm the land!

865
01:42:30,419 --> 01:42:36,603
Come father,
it's he and his second wife!

866
01:42:40,590 --> 01:42:45,498
I'm tired, I want my tea.

867
01:42:50,925 --> 01:42:53,225
The old man is childish,

868
01:42:53,431 --> 01:42:55,457
nobody listens to him,

869
01:42:55,667 --> 01:42:59,092
but he shall be kept away!

870
01:42:59,292 --> 01:43:01,622
I'm hated in this house,

871
01:43:01,826 --> 01:43:04,027
how can I be happy here?

872
01:43:04,032 --> 01:43:07,132
But... what can I do?

873
01:43:07,302 --> 01:43:09,774
I have to sit here, shut in all day,

874
01:43:09,975 --> 01:43:11,307
if I stood out there they whisper

875
01:43:11,546 --> 01:43:14,210
and look at me hatefully!

876
01:43:14,418 --> 01:43:19,290
Where can I walk in the evening?

877
01:43:19,494 --> 01:43:24,440
If I had the garden,
if I had the garden all mine;

878
01:43:24,452 --> 01:43:27,787
with singing birds in the pavillion,

879
01:43:28,388 --> 01:43:31,788
the fountain too, with fish.

880
01:43:31,798 --> 01:43:35,100
But the money...

881
01:43:35,305 --> 01:43:39,498
- Then it's money that you love.
- No no! Little Flower!

882
01:43:39,514 --> 01:43:43,846
But it will not be
easy until the harvest.

883
01:43:43,853 --> 01:43:46,815
I must see, I must see,

884
01:43:47,014 --> 01:43:49,779
my younger son keeps the accounts.

885
01:43:49,780 --> 01:43:53,585
But these're few little things.

886
01:43:53,788 --> 01:43:59,755
If you love me, if I please you.

887
01:44:01,571 --> 01:44:07,536
It shall be done! Anything! Anything!

888
01:44:08,113 --> 01:44:12,088
Be careful! My pearls!

889
01:44:50,782 --> 01:44:53,754
I may come in?

890
01:45:02,619 --> 01:45:04,486
Does my music disturb you?

891
01:45:04,723 --> 01:45:07,250
Oh no! No I like it!

892
01:45:07,462 --> 01:45:09,432
I listen sometimes.

893
01:45:09,633 --> 01:45:11,728
I play it because I'm lonely.

894
01:45:11,737 --> 01:45:14,431
I have so much to talk and laugh,

895
01:45:14,643 --> 01:45:16,840
but there's no one.

896
01:45:17,047 --> 01:45:19,710
I'm sorry, I'm very sorry!

897
01:45:19,917 --> 01:45:21,510
You must excuse me, I...

898
01:45:21,511 --> 01:45:24,599
I have some business with
the grain merchants.

899
01:45:24,608 --> 01:45:28,934
- If you'll please I must go!
- Then you'll pass by the shops?

900
01:45:29,083 --> 01:45:32,055
Yes?

901
01:45:33,058 --> 01:45:36,053
Would you mind
giving him these for a bottle?

902
01:45:36,264 --> 01:45:37,995
With silver?

903
01:45:38,201 --> 01:45:41,105
Why... Yes! Yes!

904
01:45:41,109 --> 01:45:42,777
But you won't misunderstand.

905
01:45:42,978 --> 01:45:44,771
Why should I?

906
01:45:44,775 --> 01:45:48,799
When a woman gives her slipper to a man?

907
01:45:49,002 --> 01:45:50,670
But I shouldn't tell you.

908
01:45:50,882 --> 01:45:53,184
Oh no please!

909
01:45:53,393 --> 01:45:59,367
Well then... it means
he's taking her fancy.

910
01:46:01,016 --> 01:46:05,013
But you ask me to have it guilded?

911
01:46:05,224 --> 01:46:08,248
But the bottle doesn't need guilding,

912
01:46:08,458 --> 01:46:12,406
it's pure silver!

913
01:46:38,147 --> 01:46:39,776
Here's a letter from your brother,

914
01:46:39,984 --> 01:46:42,012
will you read it to me?

915
01:46:42,022 --> 01:46:46,185
Of course mother!

916
01:46:47,300 --> 01:46:52,765
Now then, we'll hear
what our scholar has to say

917
01:46:54,180 --> 01:46:57,631
"First, I am ashamed of my ignorance.

918
01:46:57,842 --> 01:47:02,206
But I am not ashamed
to inquire of my teachers.

919
01:47:02,409 --> 01:47:05,677
Each day I learn
new ways of bring about nature's

920
01:47:05,882 --> 01:47:10,347
facts in case
nature herself should fail us".

921
01:47:11,260 --> 01:47:13,422
What does he say?

922
01:47:13,631 --> 01:47:17,092
He says
he's learning many things to help us.

923
01:47:17,306 --> 01:47:18,967
But is he happy there?

924
01:47:19,173 --> 01:47:20,864
Does he say he need anything?

925
01:47:21,070 --> 01:47:22,762
No mother.

926
01:47:22,968 --> 01:47:25,957
"I miss my beloved
father and mother deeply.

927
01:47:26,168 --> 01:47:31,657
And I'm eager to share
the happiness of our new home".

928
01:47:33,466 --> 01:47:36,740
Mother, I want to go away too!

929
01:47:36,815 --> 01:47:37,612
Go away?

930
01:47:37,817 --> 01:47:40,014
To the wars! I'll be a soldier!

931
01:47:40,222 --> 01:47:43,192
Now then what madness is this?

932
01:47:43,393 --> 01:47:47,318
Well I've heard stories
of war and plunder and battle,

933
01:47:47,519 --> 01:47:49,006
and I hate this house!

934
01:47:49,218 --> 01:47:50,778
And I'll go!

935
01:47:50,989 --> 01:47:56,956
I wish she'll stop that music!

936
01:48:18,958 --> 01:48:21,690
Now this house is full of silences.

937
01:48:22,530 --> 01:48:25,166
I was reading mother
a letter from the older brother.

938
01:48:25,469 --> 01:48:29,663
- Would you like to hear it?
- If he's well it can wait!

939
01:48:29,910 --> 01:48:33,169
But there's more
in your face than the letter!

940
01:48:33,373 --> 01:48:35,528
He'll be a soldier.

941
01:48:35,737 --> 01:48:39,571
A soldier! Now then,

942
01:48:39,775 --> 01:48:42,575
men don't take good iron to make an ail,

943
01:48:42,780 --> 01:48:45,251
nor a good man to make a soldier.

944
01:48:45,453 --> 01:48:48,289
It would be a disgrace
to me a man of serving land

945
01:48:48,493 --> 01:48:50,689
to have a son who's a soldier!

946
01:48:50,896 --> 01:48:52,696
But I'm nothing in this house!

947
01:48:52,901 --> 01:48:53,698
If you're lost in this house

948
01:48:53,903 --> 01:48:55,494
go back to the land!

949
01:48:55,702 --> 01:48:57,598
Help Ching until the harvest.

950
01:48:57,800 --> 01:48:59,660
Put an alert on yourself!

951
01:48:59,863 --> 01:49:01,489
That's good for any man!

952
01:49:01,697 --> 01:49:03,588
Well if the land
isn't fit for you anymore

953
01:49:03,601 --> 01:49:05,363
it isn't fit for me!

954
01:49:12,252 --> 01:49:16,038
Now all these stuffes I don't know.

955
01:49:16,047 --> 01:49:20,580
He's come to the age of tempers
and weeping.

956
01:49:20,784 --> 01:49:23,404
When I was a lad I had no such tempers!

957
01:49:23,612 --> 01:49:25,579
You worked on the land;

958
01:49:25,780 --> 01:49:27,749
but he's like a young lord!

959
01:49:27,950 --> 01:49:29,682
And he's been alone here.

960
01:49:29,888 --> 01:49:32,050
And you worry his age to have a bride

961
01:49:32,258 --> 01:49:35,721
But I was given a sla...

962
01:49:35,934 --> 01:49:39,874
My marriage cost my father nothing!

963
01:49:40,075 --> 01:49:43,636
The boy's our son!

964
01:49:43,844 --> 01:49:49,500
He would be better dead
than here with this woman!

965
01:49:49,707 --> 01:49:53,670
What? You're dreaming!

966
01:50:05,371 --> 01:50:11,095
Even she hears it who has nothing else;

967
01:50:11,300 --> 01:50:15,228
it feels all this house,
that woman cause

968
01:50:15,236 --> 01:50:19,140
and she's bored
and your son is young...

969
01:50:19,144 --> 01:50:20,738
Enough!

970
01:50:21,148 --> 01:50:23,715
Gossip! Kitchen gossip!

971
01:50:23,921 --> 01:50:25,413
That's where you came from!

972
01:50:25,625 --> 01:50:28,289
Where you wished to live,
live there then!

973
01:50:28,497 --> 01:50:31,923
Eat 'n sleep we will,
but between you and me

974
01:50:31,934 --> 01:50:35,481
there's nothing! Nothing!

975
01:50:48,315 --> 01:50:52,286
The man is loon here.

976
01:50:55,549 --> 01:50:57,942
What are you doing in the house?

977
01:50:58,144 --> 01:51:01,802
There's work to be done in the fields.

978
01:51:02,010 --> 01:51:05,973
But, what is it?

979
01:51:08,056 --> 01:51:10,027
You're weeping,

980
01:51:10,928 --> 01:51:15,428
and you must do it
and man can be sorry,

981
01:51:16,707 --> 01:51:18,608
But why do you weep?

982
01:51:18,810 --> 01:51:21,465
There's food for everyday.

983
01:51:21,672 --> 01:51:24,634
And fire!

984
01:51:39,631 --> 01:51:43,568
Sometimes a man gets
a longing for his fields.

985
01:51:43,769 --> 01:51:46,458
Well, if it pleases you to come up again

986
01:51:46,664 --> 01:51:49,595
and working them, they're yours!

987
01:51:49,797 --> 01:51:52,063
No it's better for my son to come;

988
01:51:52,269 --> 01:51:55,104
in the house he pulls against the yolk.

989
01:51:55,307 --> 01:51:58,975
He has all the freedom here he wants!

990
01:51:59,183 --> 01:52:00,447
Where is he today?

991
01:52:00,653 --> 01:52:01,985
He comes and goes!

992
01:52:02,189 --> 01:52:07,060
Sometimes one day, sometimes two.

993
01:52:07,263 --> 01:52:09,193
I thought you knew.

994
01:52:09,394 --> 01:52:10,686
I knew nothing!

995
01:52:10,891 --> 01:52:12,788
I spend my time in town!

996
01:52:12,990 --> 01:52:15,756
Why don't you tell me
you slow witted ox!

997
01:52:15,961 --> 01:52:18,525
Why should I tell you
what everyone's been saying?

998
01:52:18,735 --> 01:52:21,571
For weeks!

999
01:52:21,774 --> 01:52:22,799
What?

1000
01:52:22,810 --> 01:52:24,171
Well...

1001
01:52:24,180 --> 01:52:25,973
Well speak!

1002
01:52:25,983 --> 01:52:28,114
If you have eyes and ears you'll know.

1003
01:52:28,120 --> 01:52:30,425
Know? Know what?

1004
01:52:30,631 --> 01:52:32,012
That the second wife and your son is...

1005
01:52:32,218 --> 01:52:35,205
Liar!

1006
01:52:47,725 --> 01:52:50,588
Get off my land.

1007
01:52:50,589 --> 01:52:52,089
Well...

1008
01:52:52,135 --> 01:52:54,902
it's been a long time with us.

1009
01:52:55,140 --> 01:52:59,260
Take what belongs to you and go.

1010
01:52:59,466 --> 01:53:01,522
I came to you with nothing,

1011
01:53:01,731 --> 01:53:05,695
I'll go with nothing.

1012
01:53:44,225 --> 01:53:50,176
Good day master! Good day!

1013
01:54:51,057 --> 01:54:54,030
- Ah!
- Father!

1014
01:55:31,830 --> 01:55:36,995
Get out! Out of my sight!

1015
01:56:25,385 --> 01:56:28,048
Good bye mother.

1016
01:56:32,086 --> 01:56:34,086
Mother!

1017
01:56:34,187 --> 01:56:35,675
Mother, you're ill,

1018
01:56:35,687 --> 01:56:40,849
you should have a doctor.

1019
01:56:42,029 --> 01:56:45,202
It's nothing.

1020
01:56:49,044 --> 01:56:55,007
Where you go you ought to tell me.

1021
01:56:57,082 --> 01:57:01,342
They say there's a war in the north.

1022
01:57:01,548 --> 01:57:06,581
Sometimes in wars
there are those who die.

1023
01:57:06,792 --> 01:57:12,759
Well if that's best, let it be!

1024
01:57:14,474 --> 01:57:16,877
When I'm gone,
you must see to the harvest

1025
01:57:17,080 --> 01:57:18,673
we almost did it already,

1026
01:57:18,679 --> 01:57:20,672
the clerk will tell you how much.

1027
01:57:20,878 --> 01:57:24,829
I will see to it.

1028
01:57:26,544 --> 01:57:32,037
If you must go,
there's a thing to be done.

1029
01:57:32,388 --> 01:57:33,669
Speak to your father.

1030
01:57:33,878 --> 01:57:37,311
- No, no, I can't!
- You're his youngest son.

1031
01:57:51,126 --> 01:57:53,098
Father.

1032
01:57:54,299 --> 01:57:55,999
Father? I...

1033
01:57:56,103 --> 01:57:58,074
I am going away.

1034
01:57:58,075 --> 01:58:01,716
I... I only want to tell you that I...

1035
01:58:01,717 --> 01:58:05,520
how I... if you could forgive me...

1036
01:58:06,257 --> 01:58:08,418
But go!

1037
01:58:09,685 --> 01:58:13,411
Nephew! We're ruined! Everything's gone!

1038
01:58:13,618 --> 01:58:16,954
And I predicted it! I predicted it!

1039
01:58:17,157 --> 01:58:18,126
What's happened?

1040
01:58:18,327 --> 01:58:21,025
I knew it, I ran miles to tell you.

1041
01:58:21,132 --> 01:58:24,162
- What is it?
- I forgive everybody.

1042
01:58:24,238 --> 01:58:27,974
- What is it?
- This!

1043
01:58:28,180 --> 01:58:31,306
- Locusts!
- The flying plague!

1044
01:58:35,393 --> 01:58:37,859
Well! Let them come!

1045
01:58:37,863 --> 01:58:38,888
But the lion, the harvest!

1046
01:58:39,097 --> 01:58:40,794
What can we do against the gods?

1047
01:58:41,001 --> 01:58:41,970
It's not the gods!

1048
01:58:42,171 --> 01:58:43,902
It's a thing of nature! We can fight it!

1049
01:58:44,108 --> 01:58:46,873
- Have you ever seen a plague
of locusts? - No but...

1050
01:58:46,881 --> 01:58:49,743
I have! They come in millions.

1051
01:58:49,953 --> 01:58:52,652
The air is black with them and stinky.

1052
01:58:52,859 --> 01:58:55,484
And where they come down
there's nothing left!

1053
01:58:55,691 --> 01:58:58,881
Not a green of wheat!
Not a blade of grass!

1054
01:58:59,088 --> 01:59:01,350
Not a leave nor flower! Nothing!

1055
01:59:01,355 --> 01:59:03,822
And can you fight that with your book?

1056
01:59:03,927 --> 01:59:06,019
Forgive me!
I mean no disrespect for my elders,

1057
01:59:06,232 --> 01:59:07,894
but I speak for what I heard at school!

1058
01:59:08,102 --> 01:59:09,092
And I heard this:

1059
01:59:09,305 --> 01:59:10,809
"That a man is a slave to the earth,

1060
01:59:11,024 --> 01:59:13,252
or its master
and when it turns against him,

1061
01:59:13,463 --> 01:59:14,732
he must fight it!"

1062
01:59:14,937 --> 01:59:16,372
We can fight these creeping things!

1063
01:59:16,574 --> 01:59:17,836
If we save but one field,

1064
01:59:18,041 --> 01:59:19,903
it would a new thing in all this land,

1065
01:59:20,105 --> 01:59:22,296
and the best in a thousand years!

1066
01:59:22,502 --> 01:59:24,400
This thing can be done?

1067
01:59:24,603 --> 01:59:25,535
Show us how to do it!

1068
01:59:25,737 --> 01:59:31,204
If it'd please you,
come on to the fields!

1069
01:59:32,217 --> 01:59:34,688
Now look!
The locusts will come down here,

1070
01:59:34,690 --> 01:59:36,284
the wind blows between these hills.

1071
01:59:36,293 --> 01:59:39,664
There! Like a whirlpool,
if it blows the locusts

1072
01:59:39,867 --> 01:59:41,767
they'll come down there
and no other place!

1073
01:59:41,968 --> 01:59:44,693
I saw it! As a boy!
They came down there!

1074
01:59:44,899 --> 01:59:47,123
And they were gone,
with a change of wind

1075
01:59:47,330 --> 01:59:49,889
But the crops, were gone with them!

1076
01:59:50,099 --> 01:59:51,088
But that's the thing!

1077
01:59:51,302 --> 01:59:52,793
We can hold them off
till the wind changes!

1078
01:59:53,005 --> 01:59:55,307
We must take a fire break
along these hill tops.

1079
01:59:55,511 --> 01:59:56,739
Make a wall of fire!

1080
01:59:56,946 --> 01:59:58,506
But my wheat
lights on fire in a fire wall!

1081
01:59:58,716 --> 02:00:00,350
And mine! And mine! And mine!

1082
02:00:00,355 --> 02:00:02,747
I'll pay for what is eaten
and what is burnt!

1083
02:00:02,958 --> 02:00:04,656
We'll get kerosene,
bring it in carts!

1084
02:00:04,863 --> 02:00:07,020
The fire stuff,
it makes a quick, high flame.

1085
02:00:07,228 --> 02:00:09,419
We can fight everything
behind this wall!

1086
02:00:09,625 --> 02:00:10,453
If they break through,

1087
02:00:10,658 --> 02:00:12,384
we'll wind the ditch behind the fire;

1088
02:00:12,590 --> 02:00:13,615
a wall of water!

1089
02:00:13,825 --> 02:00:15,351
It will fail!

1090
02:00:15,562 --> 02:00:17,691
If it fails,
we'll fight them with torches!

1091
02:00:17,900 --> 02:00:19,631
With noise! With our hands!

1092
02:00:19,837 --> 02:00:22,163
If we can hold them off until
the wind picks them up again,

1093
02:00:22,175 --> 02:00:23,474
we can save at least those fields!

1094
02:00:23,679 --> 02:00:26,447
- It can't be done!
- It must be done!

1095
02:00:26,651 --> 02:00:29,054
All you have
and all I have depends on it!

1096
02:00:29,258 --> 02:00:30,280
You think I'm rich?

1097
02:00:30,489 --> 02:00:32,111
But if I lose
this harvest there's nothing!

1098
02:00:32,287 --> 02:00:33,717
If I save anything I'll share it!

1099
02:00:33,918 --> 02:00:35,213
Yeah! Yeah! Yeah!

1100
02:00:35,417 --> 02:00:36,849
Let the men dig and women,

1101
02:00:37,051 --> 02:00:38,987
let the old men and boys make torches,

1102
02:00:39,189 --> 02:00:40,590
gather all things that'll make a noise!

1103
02:00:40,793 --> 02:00:41,851
Bring the fire stuff!

1104
02:00:42,061 --> 02:00:44,362
Get the oxens and ploughs,
sickels, spades!

1105
02:00:44,567 --> 02:00:48,632
- Everyone! Hurry! Hurry!
- Useless! Useless!

1106
02:00:48,842 --> 02:00:51,859
I'll stay where it's safe!

1107
02:01:04,307 --> 02:01:09,275
Faster! Faster!
Make that thing wider!

1108
02:01:17,500 --> 02:01:23,047
Up here! Hurry! Hurry!
Bring the fire stuff!

1109
02:01:23,991 --> 02:01:28,154
Come on men, hurry!

1110
02:01:32,342 --> 02:01:35,314
Torches.

1111
02:02:25,808 --> 02:02:29,737
Millions! Millions!

1112
02:02:29,950 --> 02:02:32,953
My god!

1113
02:02:42,910 --> 02:02:45,304
See! They land in one place!

1114
02:02:45,514 --> 02:02:49,478
Yes, they fall!

1115
02:03:34,471 --> 02:03:40,438
Hey! Hurry with the fire stuff!

1116
02:04:04,676 --> 02:04:07,871
Load the fire stuff from here!
Get them!

1117
02:04:09,772 --> 02:04:12,187
Get the torches!

1118
02:04:23,047 --> 02:04:27,011
Get the torches!

1119
02:04:27,890 --> 02:04:31,845
Light the fires!

1120
02:05:22,607 --> 02:05:27,068
All fire stop!
They are smothering the plains!

1121
02:05:55,270 --> 02:05:58,402
It's breaking through,
just as I predicted it!

1122
02:05:58,610 --> 02:06:03,017
Just as I predicted it!

1123
02:06:03,220 --> 02:06:07,171
- Bring the water! Fill the ditches!
- Fill the ditches!

1124
02:06:16,492 --> 02:06:19,521
They'll be eaten,
there's no doubt about it now!

1125
02:06:19,730 --> 02:06:25,198
No doubt about it!
That ditch will never hold them!

1126
02:06:58,987 --> 02:07:00,419
We must fight them with our hands!

1127
02:07:00,620 --> 02:07:06,588
Ourselves! Anything! Move!

1128
02:07:41,899 --> 02:07:47,828
Chen! Keep fighting! Don't give up!

1129
02:07:51,170 --> 02:07:55,133
We must keep fighting!

1130
02:07:59,921 --> 02:08:03,918
Everyone! We can!

1131
02:08:05,761 --> 02:08:11,689
There's the wheat! Save it!

1132
02:08:18,235 --> 02:08:24,203
The wind! The wind! The wind! The wind!

1133
02:09:05,822 --> 02:09:10,302
We beat them!
We beat them! We beat them!

1134
02:09:12,344 --> 02:09:17,661
Yeah! We beat them!

1135
02:09:17,864 --> 02:09:23,314
The farm! Victory!
Victory! We've done it!

1136
02:09:39,959 --> 02:09:42,718
The young master,
it's wonderful! He did it!

1137
02:09:42,924 --> 02:09:45,352
The son and his father,
the son to be proud of!

1138
02:09:45,354 --> 02:09:46,382
The father to be proud of!

1139
02:09:46,386 --> 02:09:47,847
The wise man in 3 generations!

1140
02:09:47,854 --> 02:09:51,618
But it's nothing!
Just a matter of oil and fire,

1141
02:09:51,827 --> 02:09:54,391
something we learn from books!

1142
02:09:54,600 --> 02:09:57,437
But I'm worn out! Worn out!

1143
02:09:57,640 --> 02:09:59,200
But we saved the crops!

1144
02:09:59,410 --> 02:10:00,741
The harvest is saved!

1145
02:10:00,946 --> 02:10:04,283
The gods are good!

1146
02:10:04,486 --> 02:10:07,642
What's the matter?

1147
02:10:07,850 --> 02:10:09,770
I'll call your husband.

1148
02:10:09,781 --> 02:10:13,642
No, no! Say nothing.

1149
02:10:13,852 --> 02:10:16,253
He's on the land again,

1150
02:10:16,456 --> 02:10:22,333
with his sons, and this day's his,

1151
02:10:22,536 --> 02:10:26,271
and it must be!

1152
02:10:26,477 --> 02:10:30,931
You shall bring in the harvest,
and lead the workers!

1153
02:10:34,707 --> 02:10:37,676
Both of you!

1154
02:10:43,590 --> 02:10:48,430
And Ching is my steward!

1155
02:10:48,633 --> 02:10:50,647
Well! There's work to be done!

1156
02:10:50,861 --> 02:10:56,346
Yeah yeah yeah!
The harvest! Food! Food again!

1157
02:10:58,822 --> 02:11:02,157
And another thing must be done,
and you must do it,

1158
02:11:02,361 --> 02:11:03,489
quickly!

1159
02:11:03,697 --> 02:11:05,690
I? Work?

1160
02:11:05,702 --> 02:11:09,102
Go to the banker,
as a commisioner to be had,

1161
02:11:09,309 --> 02:11:10,870
and if you rob me a little,

1162
02:11:11,080 --> 02:11:14,779
it will be yours! For old time's sake!

1163
02:11:14,988 --> 02:11:18,044
I will sell the Great House!

1164
02:11:18,253 --> 02:11:20,808
Sell? But why?

1165
02:11:21,019 --> 02:11:23,574
The harvest is saved, you'll have money!

1166
02:11:23,783 --> 02:11:25,252
You can live like a lord!

1167
02:11:25,287 --> 02:11:28,492
All that is finished!

1168
02:11:29,094 --> 02:11:35,039
I will sell the Great House!

1169
02:11:50,178 --> 02:11:52,580
It's a wedding again!

1170
02:11:52,934 --> 02:11:53,994
But who?

1171
02:11:54,204 --> 02:11:55,934
It's your grandson's wedding!

1172
02:11:56,140 --> 02:12:01,082
And soon there'll be great grandsons!

1173
02:12:01,317 --> 02:12:03,254
Many of them! Many of them!

1174
02:12:03,455 --> 02:12:05,321
Please! Please!

1175
02:12:05,325 --> 02:12:07,855
Let him be! Let him be!

1176
02:12:08,059 --> 02:12:10,754
His cheek is as red
as this excellent wine!

1177
02:12:10,755 --> 02:12:12,052
Excellent indeed!

1178
02:12:12,054 --> 02:12:13,680
My stomach is very pleased!

1179
02:12:13,988 --> 02:12:15,422
Perhaps it's the lost of memory,

1180
02:12:15,624 --> 02:12:17,184
but I've never eaten such rice!

1181
02:12:17,395 --> 02:12:21,233
It's very bad rice.
The worst I've ever bought!

1182
02:12:21,436 --> 02:12:27,404
Grandchildren! Great grandchildren!

1183
02:12:41,611 --> 02:12:43,608
Have all the guests had rice?

1184
02:12:43,816 --> 02:12:45,750
Yes, yes!

1185
02:12:45,953 --> 02:12:49,586
Is the sweet rice is hot,
with lard and sugar?

1186
02:12:49,795 --> 02:12:50,853
And the 8 fruits?

1187
02:12:51,064 --> 02:12:52,657
It's just as you wished.

1188
02:12:52,868 --> 02:12:58,820
Mistrss! Your son's bride!

1189
02:13:04,503 --> 02:13:10,238
Well, and she's beautiful!

1190
02:13:10,448 --> 02:13:12,619
My daughter,

1191
02:13:14,120 --> 02:13:16,720
look to your husband,

1192
02:13:16,921 --> 02:13:19,521
and your husband's father,

1193
02:13:19,896 --> 02:13:24,946
and his granfather,
and you'll have no duty...

1194
02:13:24,947 --> 02:13:27,247
to any of them.

1195
02:13:33,741 --> 02:13:36,712
You must rest!

1196
02:13:43,155 --> 02:13:48,549
Everyone be here
not smiling because of me.

1197
02:14:20,046 --> 02:14:23,348
Let them be, for the bride!

1198
02:14:23,519 --> 02:14:26,789
In good time! In good time!

1199
02:14:26,994 --> 02:14:29,529
For you'll be well again.

1200
02:14:30,530 --> 02:14:32,530
Well...

1201
02:14:35,193 --> 02:14:38,319
This thing is waiting.

1202
02:14:38,328 --> 02:14:40,761
You can't speak of that,

1203
02:14:40,767 --> 02:14:43,939
and please me.

1204
02:14:44,240 --> 02:14:47,248
I'm content,

1205
02:14:48,049 --> 02:14:53,349
and what must
be done, you've done!

1206
02:15:02,257 --> 02:15:04,154
Bridegroom hasn't heard a word!

1207
02:15:04,259 --> 02:15:05,692
He's wishing we go home!

1208
02:15:05,696 --> 02:15:09,268
No! No indeed, I should be honoured
if you stay the whole evening!

1209
02:15:14,145 --> 02:15:16,673
Do you remember?

1210
02:15:16,885 --> 02:15:19,850
Yes!

1211
02:15:21,649 --> 02:15:26,445
If a man could speak, there're things...

1212
02:15:26,650 --> 02:15:30,589
Some are forgotten.

1213
02:15:31,026 --> 02:15:33,496
But now I know that you're the one,

1214
02:15:33,698 --> 02:15:39,665
that the best a man can have.

1215
02:15:49,108 --> 02:15:53,778
Ou Lang! Ou Lang!

1216
02:15:54,772 --> 02:15:57,275
This I cannot bear!

1217
02:15:57,479 --> 02:16:02,650
I'd sell all my land
if I could heal you!

1218
02:16:02,857 --> 02:16:07,816
No! I would not let you!

1219
02:16:09,159 --> 02:16:13,282
For I must die, sometime.

1220
02:16:13,490 --> 02:16:19,435
But the land will be there, after me.

1221
02:16:20,905 --> 02:16:26,872
I beg you! Stay here with me!

1222
02:16:31,387 --> 02:16:34,351
I can not!

1223
02:16:37,785 --> 02:16:40,757
Forgive me!

1224
02:17:38,654 --> 02:17:40,654
Ou Lang...

1225
02:17:41,855 --> 02:17:44,887
you are the earth!

